//Expeditious Retreat
@80000 = ~Wand of Expeditious Retreat~
@80001 = ~Upon activation, the wand doubles the wielder's normal speed for a short period of time... usually long enough to escape. Other movement-altering effects (such as Haste and Slow) cannot affect the wielder while under this effect. While Expeditious Retreat is active, the wielder cannot attack, cast spells, or use any items or special abilities... <PRO_HESHE> can only run.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Expeditious Retreat
  – Move Speed doubled
  – Attacks, spell casting, special abilities and item use are disabled
  Duration: 3 rounds
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Curse
@80002 = ~Wand of Curse~
@80003 = ~When used, the wand lowers the morale of enemy creatures and any Saving Throws and attack rolls they make by 1. At the instant the spell is completed, it affects all creatures in a 15-ft. radius centered on the point selected by the caster. Affected creatures leaving the area are still subject to the spell's effect; those entering the area after the casting is completed are not.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Charge abilities:
– Curse
  – Lowered morale
  – -1 penalty to THAC0
  – -1 penalty to saving throws
  Range: Sight
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Cause Light Wounds
@80004 = ~Wand of Cause Light Wounds~
@80005 = ~When activated, the wand charges the wielder's hand; upon touching a creature, the wielder deals 8 points of damage (save vs. Wand for half) to the creature's body. This spell has no effect on undead, constructs, or extraplanar creatures.

STATISTICS:
(Necromancy)

Charge abilities:
– Cause Light Wounds
  – Create charge to deal 8 magic damage to touched target
  – No effect on undead, constructs, or extraplanar
  Damage: 8 magic damage
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand for half damage

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~
